narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend it to architecture majors who have a strong area of interest that they would like to explore for a whole semester.
Not what the blue book describes, very out there but if you are interested in new architexture, take it!

A great course that you have the opportunity of creating your own structure as a class depending on each student's topic choosen at the beginning of the semester. The course structure was a balance of students power-points, prof commentary, and group discussions. Although I did wish to hear more from Prof Britton b/c she really is so knowledgable. You really get out what you put in as you have to do a presentation, midterm paper, and final paper all on the same subject. All in all it was a really cool class that opened my eyes to all these cool connections. Would definately recommend it if your are willing to invest the time
This was a student-driven seminar about the intersection between architecture, modernity, and religion.
YEs. If you are VERY interested in the subject.
